 \"kind\": \"proper_noun\",\n88:         \"path\": \"spec.md\",\n89:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n90:       }\n91:     ],\n92:     \"causal_summary\": \"Spec-027 hardened the Spec Kit Memory system with retrieval observability, a provenance-overwrite guard, packed BM25/BM25F lexical search, shared app-level BFS traversal, shadow feedback reducers, and soft-delete tombstones. The sibling daemon systems (`mk_skill_advisor` and `mk_code_index`) carry the same gaps that 027 closed: the advisor strips ranker evidence at output, has no manual-provenance guard on auto-edge writes, runs a token-overlap lexical lane, hand-rolls BFS, and never reuses validate outcomes; the code graph hard-deletes nodes/edges without audit, hand-rolls two BFS paths, returns no per-file chain breadcrumbs, and matches symbols by exact equality only. A ranked read-only analysis identified the ten transfers worth doing and rejected the rest.\",\n93:     \"created_at\": \"2026-06-10T19:24:08Z\",\n94:     \"last_save_at\": \"2026-06-10T19:41:16.121Z\",\n95:     \"save_lineage\": \"graph_only\",\n96:     \"last_accessed_at\": null,\n97:     \"source_docs\": [\n98:       \"spec.md\"\n99:     ],\n100:     \"last_active_child_id\": null,\n101:     \"last_active_at\": null\n102:   }\n103: }\n\n(End of file - total 103 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"schema_version\": 1,\n  \"packet_id\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph\",\n  \"spec_folder\": \"skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph\",\n  \"parent_id\": null,\n  \"children_ids\": [\n    \"skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/001-advisor-observability\",\n    \"skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/002-advisor-provenance-guard\",\n    \"skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/003-advisor-packed-bm25-lexical\",\n    \"skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adopti